    - target: {fileID: 6740536017938112096, guid: 83792a2faf1569b439953aad74536a44, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_text
      value: 'An obese 26-year-old man has an 8-hour history of severe dysuria, stranguria,
        and suprapubic and perineal pain with fever. On examination, he has suprapubic
        tenderness, and his prostate is enlarged, boggy, and exquisitely tender.
        Urinalysis shows pyuria. He continues to complain of symptoms despite insertion
        of a Foley catheter and has persistent fever following 30 hours of intravenous
        gentamicin and ampicillin. Culture grew Escherichia coli.


        What
        is the best next step?'
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
